Hi,<br />
<br />
If you go to your /Config/ folder and open <strong>ExamineIndex.config</strong>, you can specify the configuration for your various <strong>IndexSets</strong>.  Find the one called <strong>FullTextIndexSet</strong> and you can add/modify a section there called <strong>IndexUserFields</strong>.<br />
<br />
See the example below:<br />
<pre><code>&lt;IndexSet SetName=&quot;FullTextIndexSet&quot; IndexPath=&quot;~/App_Data/TEMP/ExamineIndexes/FullText/&quot;&gt;
    &lt;IndexAttributeFields&gt;
      &lt;add Name=&quot;id&quot; /&gt;
      &lt;add Name=&quot;nodeName&quot; /&gt;
      &lt;add Name=&quot;nodeTypeAlias&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/IndexAttributeFields&gt;
    &lt;IndexUserFields&gt;
        &lt;add Name=&quot;myMetaTitleAlias&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;add Name=&quot;myMetaDescriptionAlias&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/IndexUserFields&gt;
    &lt;IncludeNodeTypes /&gt;
    &lt;ExcludeNodeTypes /&gt;
&lt;/IndexSet&gt;</code></pre>

There's a very good article about how to configure Examine on the Umbraco site: <a href="http://www.example.com" rel="nofollow">http://umbraco.com/follow-us/blog-archive/2011/9/16/examining-examine</a><br />
